class Solution {
    public int findJudge(int n, int[][] trust) {
        int[] outdegree=new int[n+1];
        int[] indegree=new int[n+1];

        for(int i=0;i<trust.length;i++){
            int tw=trust[i][0];
            int wt=trust[i][1];
            outdegree[tw]++;
            indegree[wt]++;
        }
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(indegree[i]==n-1 && outdegree[i]==0){
                return i;
            }
        }
        return -1;
    }
}

Note: We are given:

n people (numbered 1 to n)

trust[i] = [a, b]
→ person a trusts person b

We must find the judge.
A person is judge if:

 Everyone else trusts them
→ indegree = n - 1

 They trust nobody
→ outdegree = 0

If no such person exists → return -1.
